        <param>
          <type>std::chrono::seconds</type>
          <declname>timeout</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Spawns <computeroutput>exe</computeroutput> with <computeroutput>args</computeroutput> as an attached child process and blocks until it exits or <computeroutput>timeout</computeroutput> elapses. On timeout the child is force-killed. Returns true iff the child ran to completion within the timeout (regardless of its exit code — caller decides what counts as success based on side effects, e.g. a written cache file). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
