        <param>
          <type>const std::string &amp;</type>
          <declname>s</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>UTF-8 std::string -&gt; std::filesystem::path. On Windows this is non-trivial: <computeroutput>path( std::string )</computeroutput> interprets the bytes as the system code page, which silently loses any character not representable in the current locale (e.g. CJK on US-Windows). On POSIX, paths are UTF-8 by convention so this is essentially a passthrough. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
